This paper deals with modeling and control of HVAC systems in commercial buildings, which involves the use of sensors, data analysis, and optimization algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which covers topics related to modeling, analysis, and control of complex systems. 

The paper also discusses the use of data-driven and physics-based models, which are relevant to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG and cs.AI). 

Furthermore, the paper addresses energy efficiency and grid stability, which are related to computational engineering (cs.CE) and emerging technologies (cs.ET). 

Overall, the paper could fit into several categories, but cs.SY is the most relevant one.
